comment: Whiteside (MIA) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with George (IND) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
RHH shows that George (IND) moves his pivot foot after ending his dribble. The official is looking for any potential illegal contact and does not pick up the pivot foot.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on Hill (IND), giving him room to avoid the contact.
George (IND) dislodges Deng (MIA) while he is airborne, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Mahinmi (IND) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Wade's (MIA) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
George (IND) sets the screen on Deng (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Deng (MIA) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Turner's (IND) post move and shot attempt.
Ellis (IND) does not inbound the ball in less than 5 seconds.
Ellis (IND) makes contact with Wade's (MIA) arms, affecting his driving shot attempt.
Hill (IND) sets the screen on Whiteside (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Wade (MIA) makes contact with Ellis's (IND) arm, affecting his shot attempt. Clock should have been reset to 1.7 sec instead of 0.8 based on the time of the contact.
Ellis (IND) cleanly strips the ball from Deng (MIA).
George's (IND) right arm is out of bounds while he is in contact with the ball.
Deng (MIA) makes contact with Mahinmi (IND), affecting his FOM away from the ball and ability to catch the pass.
Dragic (MIA) makes incidental contact with Turner (IND) after the screen.
Winslow (MIA) maintains legal guarding position as he defends George (IND) at the start of his drive, establishing position and absorbing contact when it occurs.
Mahinmi (IND) and Dragic (MIA) make incidental foot contact that causes Dragic to stumble after making the pass.
RATR shows that George (IND) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Wade (MIA) shot attempt.
Mahinmi (IND) dislodges Wade (MIA), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Winslow (MIA) continues moving as he sets the screen on Hill (IND), preventing him from disengaging after the initial contact.
Turner (IND) maintains legal guarding position as he picks up Dragic (MIA) on his drive, moving in the direction of the drive and not affecting Dragic's RSBQ. Dragic
Dragic (MIA) makes contact with Hill's (IND) body that affects his RSBQ and shot attempt.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on Hill (IND), giving him room to avoid the contact.
Mahinmi (IND) is in a legal guarding position when contact occurs with Dragic (MIA) on his shot attempt. Contact is caused by Dragic and is incidental.
Hill (IND) turns as he sets the screen on Winslow (MIA) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Deng (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends George (IND) at the start of his drive.
Deng (MIA) maintains legal guarding position when defending George's (IND) blocked shot attempt at the end of his drive.
Ellis (IND) jumps into Dragic (MIA), who has obtained a legal guarding position.
LHH shows Wade (MIA) is in a legal guarding position and that George (IND) trips on his own accord as he starts his drive.
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Winslow (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mahinmi (IND) makes contact with Dragic's (MIA) body that affects his ability to make the pass.
Turner (IND) makes contact with Winslow's (MIA) body and arm that affects his dunk attempt.
Mahinmi (IND) continues moving as he sets the screen on Winslow (MIA) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
George (IND) makes incidental contact with Wade (MIA) at the start of his drive and cleanly knocks the ball away.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on George (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Turner (IND) makes contact with Winslow's (MIA) arm, affecting his shot attempt.
Ellis (IND) commits a take foul on Wade (MIA).
Mahinmi (IND) makes contact with Dragic (MIA) that affects his RSBQ.
